@MrBrandoTheMandoI remember being in a study in middle school bc I developed compulsions after getting strep throat, and the research university was looking into a shared link between Tourette's, ADHD/autism, and OCD after childhood brain inflammation from sickness.  Apparently similar circuits in the brain as OCD can be affected bc of the urge to compulsion and the fixation on societal taboo subject matter common to both.  

I recovered in adolescence but in later adulthood went on to have non-epileptic bouts of myoclonic jerks from loud sounds or bright lights, as well as some sort of immune condition where even small infections can cause cognitive disruptions or compulsive thoughts due to incorrect brain inflammation (until the sickness is treated or clears).  It is hard when it is invisible or people deem you "disruptive."

I hope you are doing well-- thank you for sharing.  I'm glad Drinker covered this movie.  It means the word will get out and people will give it a chance.

